1 Jira Integration			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for syncing project tasks with Jira issues via the Jira REST API, supporting multiple authentication methods (API Token for Jira Cloud, Password, Personal Access Token for Jira Server/Data Center) with KeePass credential management.	information	1.1	PO-JIRA-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
7.1 Server Connection & Authentication			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall connect to Jira servers (Cloud or Data Center/Server) using the jira Python library with REST API authentication.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-JIRA-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall support three authentication methods: API Token (Jira Cloud with username + token via basic_auth), Password (legacy basic auth with username + password), and Personal Access Token (Jira Server/Data Center with token-only via token_auth).	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-JIRA-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall store server configurations as a JSON array in QSettings under the jira/servers key, with each server dict containing name, url, auth_mode (manual or keepass), credential_type (token, password, or pat), username, token (for manual mode), and keepass_entry (for keepass mode).	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-JIRA-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a test_connection(server: dict) function that returns a tuple (success: bool, error_message: str), creating a JIRA client, calling myself() for authentication verification, and recording the test result with timestamp in a module-level _last_connection_test variable.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-JIRA-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a get_jira_client(server: dict) function that returns a tuple (JIRA instance | None, error_message: str) for use in synchronization operations.	functional requirement	1.1.5	PO-JIRA-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall select authentication method based on credential_type: for "pat" use JIRA(server=url, token_auth=credential), for "token" or "password" use JIRA(server=url, basic_auth=(username, credential)).	functional requirement	1.1.6	PO-JIRA-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall validate credentials based on auth type: for PAT mode credential must be present but username is optional, for API Token or Password mode both username and credential must be present.	functional requirement	1.1.7	PO-JIRA-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall strip leading and trailing whitespace from all retrieved credentials (username and credential) from both manual settings and KeePass entries to prevent HTTP header validation errors.	functional requirement	1.1.8	PO-JIRA-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.2 Jira Servers Configuration Dialog			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall provide a Jira Servers Configuration dialog accessible from the TASK ribbon panel Jira Sync Config button, displaying a list of configured servers with Add, Edit, Delete buttons and a server details form.	functional requirement	1.2.1	PO-JIRA-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall provide authentication mode selection (Manual or KeePass) with dynamic UI showing appropriate credential fields based on the selected mode.	functional requirement	1.2.2	PO-JIRA-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall provide a Credential Type dropdown with three options: "API Token (Jira Cloud)" (credential_type=token), "Password" (credential_type=password), and "Personal Access Token (Server/Data Center)" (credential_type=pat), visible in both Manual and KeePass authentication modes.	functional requirement	1.2.3	PO-JIRA-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall update the credential field label and placeholder text dynamically based on selected credential type: "API Token:" with placeholder "API token (for Jira Cloud)" for token mode, "Password:" with placeholder "password" for password mode, and "Personal Access Token:" with placeholder "Personal Access Token (for Jira Server/Data Center)" for PAT mode.	functional requirement	1.2.4	PO-JIRA-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall include a Test Connection button that validates form inputs, builds a temporary server configuration dict, calls jira_integration.test_connection(), and displays the result in a QMessageBox with success or error details.	functional requirement	1.2.5	PO-JIRA-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Test Connection button shall validate PAT mode requirements (credential present, username optional) separately from API Token/Password mode requirements (both username and credential present).	functional requirement	1.2.6	PO-JIRA-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall support KeePass mode with three-state stack widget showing: not configured (with Configure KeePass button), locked (with Unlock KeePass button), and unlocked (with entry selector combo and New Entry button).	functional requirement	1.2.7	PO-JIRA-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira Server Edit dialog shall save credential_type to server configuration for both Manual and KeePass authentication modes.	functional requirement	1.2.8	PO-JIRA-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a get_config_summary() function that returns a dict with servers list containing name, url, auth_mode, credential_type for each server, and last_connection_test result, without exposing username, token, or keepass_entry.	functional requirement	1.2.9	PO-JIRA-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When the --debug flag is active, test_connection shall print detailed debug messages showing: server configuration, authentication mode, credential retrieval status, JIRA client creation, authentication method used (basic_auth or token_auth), and full exception tracebacks on errors.	functional requirement	1.2.10	PO-JIRA-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.3 Ribbon Panel & Menu Integration			1.3	1_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The TASK ribbon panel shall include a Jira group with a Jira Sync Config button (always enabled) positioned after the Clipboard group and before the Resource Usage tab's hidden groups list.	functional requirement	1.3.1	PO-JIRA-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
