	The SettingsManager shall provide get_jira_servers() returning list[dict], set_jira_servers(servers: list[dict]), and get_jira_credentials(server: dict) returning tuple[str, str] for username and credential.	functional requirement	1.4.10	PO-JIRA-034.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The SettingsManager.get_jira_credentials() shall strip leading and trailing whitespace from both username and credential fields retrieved from manual settings or KeePass entries.	functional requirement	1.4.11	PO-JIRA-035.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.5 Jira Sync Config Dialog – JQL Filter			1.5	1_5_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall include a JQL Filter text input field for specifying a Jira Query Language filter string (e.g., "project = MYPROJECT AND status = 'In Progress'") to determine which issues are synced.	functional requirement	1.5.1	PO-JIRA-036.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JQL Filter field shall display a comprehensive tooltip with JQL syntax examples covering project filters, status filters, assignee filters, date range filters, priority filters, labels, components, and combined filters.	functional requirement	1.5.2	PO-JIRA-037.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JQL Filter field shall include a Test Filter button that validates the server selection and filter text, connects to the selected Jira server, executes jira.search_issues(filter_text, maxResults=50), and displays the number of matching issues and a summary of the first 10 in a QMessageBox.	functional requirement	1.5.3	PO-JIRA-038.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Test Filter button shall validate that a server is selected and a filter is specified before attempting to connect.	functional requirement	1.5.4	PO-JIRA-039.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Test Filter button shall display a wait cursor during the connection and filter execution, restoring the normal cursor when complete or on error.	functional requirement	1.5.5	PO-JIRA-040.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JQL Filter field, filter type, and field-selection state shall be stored per-project in enterprise custom properties (sidecar .custom-props.json file) inside a single JSON container value under the key "jira2project", making all Jira sync settings portable with the project file.	functional requirement	1.5.6	PO-JIRA-041.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JQL Filter field shall be disabled when no project is open, with a hint message informing the user that filters are project-specific.	functional requirement	1.5.7	PO-JIRA-042.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall load the saved filter from project custom properties when initialized with a project parameter, displaying it in the filter text field.	functional requirement	1.5.8	PO-JIRA-043.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall save the filter text to project custom properties when the user clicks OK and a project is open, preserving existing custom properties.	functional requirement	1.5.9	PO-JIRA-044.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The MainWindow.open_jira_config() method shall pass the current project instance to the JiraSyncConfigDialog and call _mark_dirty() when the dialog is accepted with a project open, triggering custom properties save.	functional requirement	1.5.10	PO-JIRA-045.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a record_filter_test(server_name: str, filter_text: str, issue_count: int, error: str) function that records filter test results with timestamp, success status, and error message in a module-level _last_filter_test variable for diagnostic purposes.	functional requirement	1.5.11	PO-JIRA-046.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog._test_filter() method shall call record_filter_test() after each filter test attempt (successful or failed), recording the server name, filter text, issue count, and error message.	functional requirement	1.5.12	PO-JIRA-047.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The get_config_summary() function shall include the last_filter_test result when available, containing server_name, filter, issue_count, timestamp, success, and error fields.	functional requirement	1.5.13	PO-JIRA-048.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.6 Jira Sync Config Dialog – Saved Filter Support			1.6	1_6_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall include a Filter Type selector with two radio buttons: "JQL" (raw JQL string) and "Saved Filter (ID or URL)" (a Jira saved filter referenced by numeric ID or full filter URL).	functional requirement	1.6.1	PO-JIRA-051.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When "JQL" is selected as the filter type, the filter input field shall display a placeholder and tooltip with JQL syntax examples; when "Saved Filter (ID or URL)" is selected it shall display a placeholder and tooltip describing the accepted formats (numeric ID or full ?filter= URL).	functional requirement	1.6.2	PO-JIRA-052.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The filter type selection shall be persisted per-project inside the "jira2project" JSON container as the "filter_type" key (value: "jql" or "filter"), stored together with the filter text in the same container.	functional requirement	1.6.3	PO-JIRA-053.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When loading filter settings from project custom properties, the JiraSyncConfigDialog shall JSON-parse the "jira2project" container, read the "filter_type" key from the parsed dict, and pre-select the corresponding radio button, defaulting to "jql" when the key is absent or contains an unrecognised value; for backward compatibility it shall also accept the legacy flat key "JIRA Sync Filter Type" when the container is absent.	functional requirement	1.6.4	PO-JIRA-054.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When the filter input is cleared and saved, the "jira2project" container shall be written without the "filter" and "filter_type" keys (other container fields such as field selections are preserved).	functional requirement	1.6.5	PO-JIRA-055.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Both Filter Type radio buttons shall be disabled when no project is open, matching the disabled state of the filter input field.	functional requirement	1.6.6	PO-JIRA-056.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a _extract_filter_id(value: str) helper that extracts a numeric Jira filter ID from a full ?filter= URL, a filter=ID query string fragment, or a plain numeric string, returning an empty string when no ID can be found.	functional requirement	1.6.7	PO-JIRA-057.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira integration shall expose a resolve_filter_to_jql(jira, filter_value: str, filter_type: str) function that, for filter_type="jql", returns the value unchanged; for filter_type="filter", calls jira.filter(id).jql to retrieve the JQL of a saved filter and returns it together with an empty error string, or returns ("", error_message) on failure.	functional requirement	1.6.8	PO-JIRA-058.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Test Filter button shall, when the selected server uses KeePass authentication and the KeePass database is locked, present a QMessageBox.question asking the user whether to unlock KeePass now, and abort the test if the user declines.	functional requirement	1.6.9	PO-JIRA-059.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If the user accepts the KeePass unlock prompt in Test Filter, the system shall attempt auto_unlock_keepass() first; if that fails, it shall prompt for the master password via QInputDialog, show a warning on failure, and abort the test.	functional requirement	1.6.10	PO-JIRA-060.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When filter_type is "filter", Test Filter shall call resolve_filter_to_jql() to obtain the JQL before executing jira.search_issues(); if resolution fails it shall display a "Filter Resolution Failed" error dialog and record the error via record_filter_test() without executing the search.	functional requirement	1.6.11	PO-JIRA-061.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When filter_type is "filter" and the test succeeds, the Test Filter result dialog shall include the resolved JQL string alongside the issue count summary.	functional requirement	1.6.12	PO-JIRA-062.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.7 Jira Sync Config Dialog – Field Mapping & Layout			1.7	1_7_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The file_handler module shall transparently expand JSON-object string values in the sidecar .custom-props.json file into nested dicts on save (any value whose string representation starts with "{") and re-serialize nested dicts back to JSON strings on load, so that the "jira2project" container is stored as a readable nested object in the sidecar file while the MPXJ HashMap always receives a plain JSON string.	functional requirement	1.7.1	PO-JIRA-063.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall implement cross-field dependency rules for the Jira→Project field-selection tab via the module-level `_JIRA2PROJECT_FIELD_DEPENDENCIES` mapping: the dependent checkboxes `jira_status_percent`, `jira_resolution_date`, `jira_assignee_display_name`, `jira_reporter_display_name`, `jira_fix_version_description`, `jira_fix_version_released`, `jira_fix_version_start_date`, `jira_fix_version_release_date`, `jira_time_spent_seconds`, and `jira_worklog_entries` shall each be automatically disabled and unchecked when their respective controller checkbox (`jira_status`, `jira_resolution`, `jira_assignee`, `jira_reporter`, `jira_fix_versions`, or `jira_time_spent`) is unchecked; each dependent checkbox shall be re-enabled when its controller is re-checked.	functional requirement	1.7.2	PO-JIRA-064.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall constrain its maximum height to QApplication.desktop().availableGeometry().height() minus a 40 px chrome buffer so that the OK/Cancel button row is always fully visible on screen regardless of screen resolution or taskbar height.	functional requirement	1.7.3	PO-JIRA-065.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The JiraSyncConfigDialog shall wrap the content of each tab (Jira → Project and Project → Jira) in a QScrollArea with setWidgetResizable(True) and QFrame.NoFrame, so that all tab content is reachable by scrolling within the tab without expanding the dialog beyond its maximum height.	functional requirement	1.7.4	PO-JIRA-066.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
7.8 Server Capabilities Query			1.8	1_8_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The Jira integration shall expose a fetch_server_capabilities(server: dict, project_key: str = "") function that returns a dict with three keys: issue_types (sorted list of issue type name strings available on the server), priorities (sorted list of priority name strings), and error (non-empty string when the server cannot be reached or authentication fails; empty string on success). When project_key is supplied the issue types shall be fetched for that specific project via the Jira createmeta endpoint; if that call fails or no project key is given the function shall fall back to the global issue_types() endpoint. A failure of the priorities() endpoint shall not prevent issue_types from being returned.	functional requirement	1.8.1	PO-JIRA-067.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
2 Jira → Project Sync			2	2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for the runtime Jira-to-Project synchronisation engine (integrations/jira_sync.py) that reads Jira issues via the configured filter and creates or updates MPXJ tasks in the open project file. The configuration (server, filter, field selection) is managed by JiraSyncConfigDialog and stored in the jira2project custom-properties container; these requirements cover only the sync execution logic.	information	2.1	PO-J2P-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
8.1 Jira → Project Sync Engine			2.1	2_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	All values received from Jira and written to a task during sync shall be persisted in the .custom-props.json sidecar file (the task JSON prop file).	functional requirement	2.1.1	PO-J2P-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The synced values for a task shall be stored as a nested JSON object under the key "jira" inside the per-task custom property entry in the sidecar; the Jira issue key used as the lookup identifier shall be stored under the sub-key "jira_key" within that object.	functional requirement	2.1.2	PO-J2P-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Only field values whose flag is enabled in the sync configuration (jira2project.fields.<field_name> == true) shall be written to the sidecar; essential fields (jira_key, jira_issue_type, jira_project_key) shall always be stored regardless of the field-selection checkboxes.	functional requirement	2.1.3	PO-J2P-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync configuration shall support the following 34 boolean field flags in the jira2project.fields sub-dict: jira_project_name, jira_description, jira_status, jira_status_percent, jira_resolution, jira_resolution_date, jira_security_level, jira_assignee, jira_assignee_display_name, jira_reporter, jira_reporter_display_name, jira_priority, jira_due_date, jira_created_date, jira_updated_date, jira_components, jira_fix_versions, jira_affects_versions, jira_fix_version_description, jira_fix_version_released, jira_fix_version_start_date, jira_fix_version_release_date, jira_labels, jira_environment, jira_votes, jira_comments, jira_time_spent, jira_remaining_estimate, jira_original_estimate, jira_time_spent_seconds, jira_worklog_entries, jira_parent_key, jira_epic_link, jira_parent_link, jira_subtask_parent, jira_issue_links.	functional requirement	2.1.4	PO-J2P-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All 34 field flags shall default to false when not explicitly saved in the configuration.	functional requirement	2.1.5	PO-J2P-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When the jira_status_percent flag is enabled, the Jira issue status name shall be mapped to a numeric "% Complete" value and applied to the MPXJ task.	functional requirement	2.1.6	PO-J2P-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Multi-value fields (jira_components, jira_fix_versions, jira_affects_versions, jira_labels) shall be stored as comma-separated strings in the sidecar.	functional requirement	2.1.7	PO-J2P-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	For each Jira issue returned by the configured filter, the sync engine shall look up whether a matching task already exists in the project by comparing the issue key against the jira_key value stored in each task's sidecar entry.	functional requirement	2.1.8	PO-J2P-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The lookup shall be performed by building a dictionary mapping every jira_key value found in the sidecar data to its corresponding MPXJ task object at the start of each sync run.	functional requirement	2.1.9	PO-J2P-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	A task shall be considered a match if its sidecar jira_key value equals the issue key of the Jira issue being processed; the comparison shall be exact (case-sensitive).	functional requirement	2.1.10	PO-J2P-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If no matching task exists for a Jira issue, a new MPXJ task shall be created and the result shall be counted as "created".	functional requirement	2.1.11	PO-J2P-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The new task name shall be set to the Jira issue summary.	functional requirement	2.1.12	PO-J2P-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Jira issue key shall always be saved to the new task's sidecar property jira_key (essential field, written regardless of field flags).	functional requirement	2.1.13	PO-J2P-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If the jira_assignee field flag is enabled and the Jira issue has an assignee, a resource assignment shall be created in MPXJ using the assignee display name; if the flag is disabled or the issue has no assignee, the task shall be created without any resource assignment.	functional requirement	2.1.14	PO-J2P-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All other enabled field values shall be written to the task sidecar on task creation.	functional requirement	2.1.15	PO-J2P-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If a matching task already exists, its properties shall be updated with the current values received from Jira and the result shall be counted as "updated".	functional requirement	2.1.16	PO-J2P-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The task name shall be updated to the current Jira issue summary on every sync run (the task name always tracks the latest Jira ticket summary).	functional requirement	2.1.17	PO-J2P-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	All enabled field values shall be re-written to the task sidecar on update; values for disabled flags shall not be modified or removed.	functional requirement	2.1.18	PO-J2P-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The resource assignment shall be updated according to the jira_assignee flag in the same way as for new tasks: create or update the assignment when the flag is enabled, leave the current assignment unchanged when the flag is disabled.	functional requirement	2.1.19	PO-J2P-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When a Jira issue is of type Epic (detected via issue.fields.issuetype.name == "Epic"), it shall be created or updated as an MPXJ summary task with the Summary and Rollup properties set to 1 at the appropriate WBS outline level.	functional requirement	2.1.20	PO-J2P-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Sub-tickets that belong to an Epic (identified by fields.parent.key matching the Epic issue key on modern Jira, or customfield_10014 on older Jira instances) shall be placed as child tasks one WBS outline level below the Epic summary task, wired via MPXJ task.setParentTask().	functional requirement	2.1.21	PO-J2P-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The task name for both Epic container tasks and their sub-tickets shall be set to the Jira issue summary without any prefix or abbreviation.	functional requirement	2.1.22	PO-J2P-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The issue_type_labels mapping (stored as a JSON dict in the jira2project configuration under "issue_type_labels") shall be retained for future use but shall not influence the task name written to the project.	functional requirement	2.1.23	PO-J2P-023.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	During sync the engine shall process Epics before their sub-tickets so that the parent summary task always exists before child tasks are appended to it.	functional requirement	2.1.24	PO-J2P-024.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If an Epic's summary task already exists in the project (matched via jira_key on the summary task), sub-tickets shall be looked up among the existing children of that summary task by jira_key before creating new child tasks.	functional requirement	2.1.25	PO-J2P-025.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The _normalize_jira_datetime(date_str) function shall convert a Jira ISO-8601 datetime string that contains a 'T' separator and a timezone offset (or 'Z') to a UTC ISO-8601 string with a 'Z' suffix; strings without a 'T' separator (date-only strings) shall be returned unchanged; empty or None inputs shall be returned unchanged.	functional requirement	2.1.26	PO-J2P-042.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When the jira_created_date, jira_updated_date, or jira_resolution_date field flags are enabled in the jira2project sync configuration, the sync engine shall call _normalize_jira_datetime() on the raw Jira field value before storing it in the task sidecar, so that all stored date-time values are in UTC ISO-8601 format with a 'Z' suffix.	functional requirement	2.1.27	PO-J2P-043.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
