	When is_debug() is True, the sync function shall emit a structured [DEBUG] log line prefixed with "[DEBUG] jira2project_sync.run:" for each processed Jira issue.	functional requirement	2.3.2	PO-J2P-031.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	For task creation the debug log line shall include the action token [CREATE], the Jira issue key, and the issue summary.	functional requirement	2.3.3	PO-J2P-032.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	For task update the debug log line shall include the action token [UPDATE], the Jira issue key, and the issue summary.	functional requirement	2.3.4	PO-J2P-033.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync module shall maintain a module-level _last_result variable storing the result dict of the most recent sync run, accessible via a public get_last_result() function.	functional requirement	2.3.5	PO-J2P-034.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Before calling get_jira_client() to initiate a "Sync from Jira" operation, the button handler shall check whether the selected server uses KeePass authentication and the KeePass database is currently locked; if so, it shall present a QMessageBox.question asking the user to unlock now, attempt auto_unlock_keepass() first, fall back to a QInputDialog password prompt, and abort the sync if the database cannot be unlocked or the user declines.	functional requirement	2.3.6	PO-J2P-036.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync engine shall fetch all Jira issues matching the configured filter by paginating through the Jira REST API in pages of 100 issues until no further results are returned, so that result sets larger than any single page limit are fully imported.	functional requirement	2.3.7	PO-J2P-037.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync engine shall request only the specific Jira fields required for sync (summary, issuetype, status, parent, customfield_10014, duedate, assignee, description, priority) rather than all fields, in order to reduce response payload size and prevent HTTP 504 Gateway Timeout errors on large result sets.	functional requirement	2.3.8	PO-J2P-038.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When advanced.relink.behavior is set to 'messagebox' in the jira2project configuration, run_sync shall invoke relink_callback(issue_key, stored_task_uid, incoming_task_uid) if a non-None callback was supplied and shall use the returned string ('skip' or 'relink') to decide the action; if no callback is supplied, the behavior shall default to 'skip'.	functional requirement	2.3.9	PO-J2P-044.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When advanced.conflict.policy is set to 'messagebox' in the jira2project configuration, run_sync shall invoke conflict_callback(issue_key, task_name) if a non-None callback was supplied and shall use the returned string ('prefer_jira', 'prefer_local', or 'skip') to resolve the conflict; if no callback is supplied, the behavior shall default to 'skip'.	functional requirement	2.3.10	PO-J2P-045.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When advanced.orphan.behavior is set to 'messagebox' in the jira2project configuration, run_sync shall invoke orphan_callback(jira_key, task_name) if a non-None callback was supplied and shall use the returned string ('keep', 'unlink', 'delete', or 'close') to handle the orphaned task; if no callback is supplied, the behavior shall default to 'keep'.	functional requirement	2.3.11	PO-J2P-046.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
