	The Project → Jira tab shall include a Create/Update Mode selector with three options: "Create Only" (create new Jira issues for unmatched tasks), "Update Only" (update existing matched Jira issues), and "Create and Update" (perform both create and update operations).	functional requirement	3.1.3	PO-P2J-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project → Jira tab shall include a Conflict Policy selector with at least two options: "Manual Review" (pause on conflicts and prompt the user) and "Prefer Jira" (resolve conflicts automatically in favour of Jira data).	functional requirement	3.1.4	PO-P2J-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project → Jira tab shall include a Dry Run checkbox; when checked the export operation shall be simulated without making any changes to the Jira server, allowing the user to preview the actions that would be taken.	functional requirement	3.1.5	PO-P2J-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project → Jira tab shall include a Field Map table in which each row maps a project field name to a target Jira field name; the table shall support Add, Edit, and Delete row operations.	functional requirement	3.1.6	PO-P2J-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project → Jira tab shall include an Issue Type Map table mapping project task type names to Jira issue type names; the table shall support Add, Edit, and Delete row operations.	functional requirement	3.1.7	PO-P2J-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project → Jira tab shall include a Transition Map table mapping project task status values to Jira transition IDs or transition names; the table shall support Add, Edit, and Delete row operations.	functional requirement	3.1.8	PO-P2J-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On accepting the JiraSyncConfigDialog, the Project → Jira export settings (export_scope, create_update_mode, conflict_policy, dry_run, fields, issue_type_map, transition_map) shall be persisted per-project as a JSON container value under the key "project2jira" in the enterprise custom properties sidecar, using the same HashMap mechanism as the "jira2project" container.	functional requirement	3.1.9	PO-P2J-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
