	When a Jira server is selected and accessible, the JiraSyncConfigDialog shall perform a best-effort server capability check for issue types by calling jira_client.issue_types(); it shall display an error listing any mapped issue type names not found on the server and refuse to save when unknown types are detected.	functional requirement	3.2.5	PO-P2J-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When a Jira server is selected and accessible and a non-empty Transition Map is configured, the JiraSyncConfigDialog shall perform a best-effort transition capability check: for each mapped Jira issue type it shall retrieve available transitions from a sample issue via jira_client.transitions() and reject any mapped transition ID or name not found among the available transitions, displaying an error and refusing to save.	functional requirement	3.2.6	PO-P2J-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
9.3 Project → Jira Push Engine			3.3	3_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for the runtime Project-to-Jira push execution engine (integrations/jira_sync.py — run_push_to_jira). The configuration (export_scope, create_update_mode, conflict_policy, dry_run, fields, issue_type_map, transition_map) is read from the project2jira custom-properties container; these requirements cover only the push execution logic.	information	3.3	PO-P2J-INFO-002.0	Not relevant		
9.3.1 Push Execution			3.3.1	3_3_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall expose a run_push_to_jira(project, server, jira_client, sidecar_path, included_task_uids=None) function that returns a result dict with keys: created (int), updated (int), transitioned (int), skipped (int), errors (list[str]), log (list[str]), preview_actions (list[dict]), and dry_run (bool).	functional requirement	3.3.1.1	PO-P2J-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When dry_run is True in the project2jira config, the push engine shall collect a list of preview_actions dicts without calling any write API on the Jira client; each entry shall include task_uid, task_name, jira_key ("NEW" for unlinked tasks), action ("create" or "update"), issue_type, changed_fields, and details.	functional requirement	3.3.1.2	PO-P2J-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	For each eligible task that has no existing Jira link, the push engine shall apply the unlinked_task_behavior policy: "skip" increments the skipped counter and logs a [SKIP] entry; "create" (or "prompt" treated as create) proceeds to create a new Jira issue.	functional requirement	3.3.1.3	PO-P2J-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When an unlinked task is eligible for creation, the push engine shall call jira_client.create_issue(fields=…), record the new key and id in both task_jira and task_p2j sidecar sections, increment the created counter, and append a [CREATE] log entry.	functional requirement	3.3.1.4	PO-P2J-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When a task is linked to an existing Jira issue (jira_key present in task_jira or task_p2j sidecar), the push engine shall call jira_client.issue(key).update(fields=…) with the current field payload, increment the updated counter, and append an [UPDATE] log entry.	functional requirement	3.3.1.5	PO-P2J-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After a create or update action, if the task's status string (derived from percentage complete) matches a key in the transition_map, the push engine shall resolve the transition ID via jira_client.transitions(key) and call jira_client.transition_issue(key, transition_id), incrementing the transitioned counter and appending a [TRANSITION] log entry.	functional requirement	3.3.1.6	PO-P2J-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When conflict_policy is not "prefer_project" and the task has an existing Jira link, the push engine shall call jira_client.issue(key, fields="updated,summary") and compare remote_updated against task_p2j[uid].last_pushed_at; when remote_updated is newer, the conflict policy shall be applied: "prefer_jira" skips the update; "manual_review" skips and appends an error message.	functional requirement	3.3.1.7	PO-P2J-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When hierarchy_export.enabled is True and a task's parent task has an existing Jira key, the push engine shall call jira_client.issue(child_key).update(fields={"parent": {"key": parent_key}}) to set the parent link in Jira.	functional requirement	3.3.1.8	PO-P2J-023.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When the included_task_uids parameter is not None, the push engine shall restrict processing to only tasks whose unique-ID string is present in the set; all other eligible tasks shall be silently excluded.	functional requirement	3.3.1.9	PO-P2J-024.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The push engine shall expose a _with_retry(fn, max_retries, backoff_seconds) helper that calls fn(); on transient Jira errors (HTTP 429, 500, 502, 503, timeout, connection errors) it shall retry up to max_retries times with exponential backoff; non-transient exceptions shall propagate immediately on the first attempt.	functional requirement	3.3.1.10	PO-P2J-025.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After all tasks are processed, the push engine shall update the sidecar with task_jira, task_p2j, and jira_push_meta sections (last_run_at, last_result summary, last_successful_push when no errors) and write the sidecar to disk unless dry_run is True.	functional requirement	3.3.1.11	PO-P2J-026.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When auditability.enabled is True and dry_run is False, the push engine shall append an audit session entry to jira_push_meta.audit_sessions containing run_at, created, updated, transitioned, skipped, failed, reasons (up to 20 errors), and details (up to 100 per-task results); the audit_sessions list shall be capped at 20 entries.	functional requirement	3.3.1.12	PO-P2J-027.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The push module shall maintain a module-level _last_push_result variable storing the result dict of the most recent run_push_to_jira() call, accessible via a public get_last_push_result() function that returns None when no push has been executed in the current session.	functional requirement	3.3.1.13	PO-P2J-028.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
